<?TBLROW 1>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">March, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The Canada Revenue Agency (&ldquo;CRA&rdquo;) begins an audit of the Respondents and their companies</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 2>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">August 17, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The auditor, Glen Foster, refers the case to the CRA criminal investigations unit. The case is accepted for full investigation.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 3>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 2007</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Searches under warrant are executed at the Respondents' home and businesses, their accountant's office and the CRA auditor's desk. The Respondents' bookkeeper, Deborah Ferens, is interviewed by CRA investigator Terry Finlay during the search of their accountant's office.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 4>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">December 2007</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The Public Prosecution Service of Canada Economic Crimes Group (&ldquo;PPSC&rdquo;) receives a draft prosecution report prepared by the CRA investigator, Keith Kendal, alleging that the Respondents and their companies are failing to include cash amounts in reported income. Senior Counsel Janna Hyman reviews the draft prosecution report, then refers it to Counsel Lisa McLean for an initial assessment of whether criminal charges are justified.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 5>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 10, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Ms. McLean drafts a memo recommending that Brian Jones be appointed as agent prosecutor.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 6>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 14, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Ms. McLean begins preparing a draft Charge Approval memo recommending charges proceed against Tony Samaroo and MGM Restaurants Ltd. (&ldquo;MGM&rdquo;) but not Helen Samaroo or Samaroo Holdings Ltd. (&ldquo;SHL&rdquo;) at that time.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 7>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 22, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Mr. Jones is appointed as agent for the Director of Public Prosecutions to prosecute charges under s. 239(1)(a) and (d) of the <EM>Income Tax Act</EM> (&ldquo;<EM>ITA</EM>&rdquo;) against Tony Samaroo, Helen Samaroo, MGM and SHL.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 8>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Mid-February, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Ms. Hyman became supervising PPSC counsel on the prosecution.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 9>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">March 18, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Mr. Kendal's final prosecution report (the &ldquo;Prosecution Report&rdquo;) was approved by the CRA and forwarded to Ms. Hyman and Mr. Jones.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 10>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">April 28, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Ms. Hyman directed that the prosecution proceed summarily.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 11>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">June 12, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">A 21-count Information prepared in Brian Jones' office was sworn by Keith Kendal charging Tony and Helen Samaroo individually, as corporate directors and as parties with each other, under <EM>ITA</EM> ss. 239(1)(a) and (d) with filing false tax returns and tax evasion.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 12>
