<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="4"><BOLD>Civil Audit and Criminal Investigation</BOLD></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 2>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1" COLSEP="VDOT">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSEP="VDOT"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3" COLSEP="VDOT"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 3>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">March, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">The respondents are audited by the CRA. Mr. Glen Foster, the civil auditor, interviews Deborah Ferens, the respondents' bookkeeper; Ed Heese, the accountant; and Tony Samaroo.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 4>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 5>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Mr. Samaroo and Mr. Heese explain to Mr. Foster that the source of the deposits to the business accounts was cash savings that Mr. Samaroo had accumulated over many years. Both explained that Mr. Samaroo was afraid the bank would stop accepting old $100 bills, so he had deposited the bills into the business accounts. Mr. Heese confirmed that Mr. Samaroo had told him in 2005&mdash;long before the start of the civil audit&mdash;that he had been depositing his old $100 bills into his personal and corporate accounts.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 6>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 7>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">August 18, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Glen Foster finishes his audit and refers the case to the Enforcement Division of the CRA for determination as to whether a criminal investigation will be undertaken.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 8>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 9>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">October 30, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Alan Jones, with the CRA, prepares a Primary Report recommending that the case proceed to a full investigation and searches be conducted at the residence, businesses and accountant's office. He identifies two other factors that justified the case being selected for criminal investigation: 1. The restaurant and nightclub industries are those that have a high rate of non-compliance; and, 2. CRA had not prosecuted a business in the restaurant or nightclub industry in the Nanaimo area recently.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 10>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 11>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 24, 2007</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">The search warrants in respect to the respondents' residence, businesses and Mr. Heese's office are executed. Mr. Terry Finlay, an investigator with the CRA, interviews Deborah Ferens, the bookkeeper for the respondents. He does so based on pre-prepared, type written questions. Ms. Ferens tells Mr. Finlay that she does not look at the till tapes or source documents provided by the respondents. In other words, she does not know how many till tapes she is being provided with, or what information is represented on the daily sales summary sheet. Mr. Kendal testified that he understood her explanation to mean that she did not look at the till tapes and could not say whether she received two or three tapes, or what shifts they related to.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 12>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 13>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 25, 2007</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Keith Kendal is assigned to lead the investigation. He knows by this point the CRA has no till tapes and quickly becomes aware of the Finlay interview of Ms. Ferens. He spends the next several weeks planning his investigation and reviewing the fruits of the searches to determine what information the CRA has and does not have.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 14>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 15>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">February 25, 2007 (approx.)</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Approximately 1 month after the execution of the search warrants, Mr. Kendal creates a working paper entitled &ldquo;Investigations Plan-MGM&rdquo;. In it, he writes that CRA &ldquo;cannot show that only two ring ups (sic) were reported on 2004 &amp; 2005&rdquo;. The appellant formally admitted that this statement accurately reflected Mr. Kendal's view of the case at the time.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 16>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 17>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Mr. Kendal also wrote in the working paper he was planning on issuing a Production Order for prior years &ldquo;to deflect the defence of a lifetime of savings&rdquo; and that he intended to &ldquo;defuse Defence position: Accumulated 35 years of cash being deposited in these years?&rdquo;</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 18>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 19>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Prior to January 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Mr. Kendal prepares his draft Prosecution Report. He states that &ldquo;interviews with the bookkeeper will show that she only received two till tapes per day from the Samaroos, not the three that were actually produced in the normal course of the business day&rdquo;. No mention is made of the Finlay interview of Ms. Ferens.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 20>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 21>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="4"><BOLD>Referral of the Draft Prosecution Report to PPSC</BOLD></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 22>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1" COLSEP="VDOT">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 23>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Early January 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Mr. Kendal forwards his draft Prosecution Report to Brian Jones, who provides it to PPSC. Lisa Mclean, sernior counsel on behalf of PPSC, speaks with Brian Jones and Keith Kendal by telephone.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 24>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 25>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 10, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Ms. Mclean speaks to Kendal by phone. She writes that Kendal told her:</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 26>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 27>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">&ldquo;He can show he's got it; can't really show when earned it.&rdquo;</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 28>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 29>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 10, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Lisa McLean prepares a memorandum recommending that Brian Jones be appointed as agent prosecutor.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 30>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 31>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 14, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Lisa McLean prepares her draft charge approval memorandum, the only written legal analysis ever prepared about the case. She writes that no charges can be approved until Ms. Ferens' is interviewed and her evidence confirmed. Both Jana Hyman and Bruce Harper agree with Ms. Mclean's position.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 32>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 33>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">In her memorandum, Ms. McLean writes that Helen Samaroo should not be charged with either personal evasion or in respect to the corporate evasion. She also indicates that Deborah Ferens needs to be interviewed before charges can be approved.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 34>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 35>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 14, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Lisa McLean communicates PPSC's position to Mr. Kendal and he agrees to interview Deborah Ferens. He again fails to mention the Finlay interview.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 36>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 37>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">January 15, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Lisa McLean emails Brian Jones and tells him that there is more work to be done including interviewing Deborah Ferens. She writes: &ldquo;we decided that this work should be done before charges are approved&rdquo;.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 38>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 39>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">February 4, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Keith Kendal contacts Ed Heese and Deborah Ferens to arrange interviews. Shortly before the interviews he is advised that all requests for information should be directed through their lawyer, Mr. George Jones. Mr. Kendal testified that he only wanted to proceed if he could interview Ms. Ferens in person. He gave no reason for taking that position.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 40>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="3"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="4"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 41>
<TBLROW ROWSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">February 11, 2008</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="3">Mr. Kendal speaks with Lisa McLean and tells her the bookkeeper had refused to be interviewed. He again fails to tell Ms. McLean that Deborah Ferens had already been interviewed by Mr. Finlay, and had made it clear she could not provide evidence that a shift was unreported, or if it that was the case, which one.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 42>
<TBLROW>
